First, let's find the intersection (A∩B) and the symmetric difference (A∆B) of sets A and B.

A = {1, 2, 3}
B = {2, 3, 4}

A∩B = {2, 3} (elements common to both A and B)

A∆B = {1, 4} (elements in A or B but not in both)

Now, let's find the symmetric difference of (A∩B) and (A∆B).

(A∩B) = {2, 3}
(A∆B) = {1, 4}

The symmetric difference of (A∩B) and (A∆B) is the set of elements in either (A∩B) or (A∆B) but not in both.

Symmetric difference of (A∩B) and (A∆B) = {1, 2, 3, 4}
